  "method": [
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Slice the ginger and crush with the back of a knife. Then roughly chop it up. Crush the spring onion whites with the back of a knife and roughly chop them up. Add them to a pot with the oats and Rude Health Coconut Drink. Cook on a low heat for 15 mins until the porridge is thick and cooked."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Meanwhile, finely chop the rest of the spring onions and coriander."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Finish with the shaoxing wine and soy sauce."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Thinly slice the garlic cloves and add them to a pan with some olive oil. Cook on a very low heat until just started to turn golden. Crack in the eggs and cook until the whites are crispy but the yolk is still soft."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Pour your porridge into a bowl and place your crispy egg on top."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Then sprinkle your crispy onions, chilli oil, spring onions and coriander on top. Drizzle over some sesame oil. Break open the egg yolk, mix it all together and enjoy."
    }
  ],
